properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Significant precipitation expected tonight, persisting into Sunday for some areas. Total snowfall: 15-35 cm for northern New Brunswick. Total rainfall: Near 25 mm for areas near the Fundy coast. Locations: New Brunswick. Time span: Tonight through to Sunday morning. Remarks: Snow and ice pellets are expected across northern New Brunswick with rain over southern New Brunswick tonight. Snow, freezing rain or ice pellets are forecast for the remaining areas of the province tonight, with a changeover to rain possible. Snowfall warnings are in effect over northern parts of the province while rainfall warnings are in effect for some southern areas. Conditions across the province will begin to improve on Sunday. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NBstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NBStorm.

properties.Title: Storm Surge Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: High Storm Surge levels and large waves are expected to impact the coast. Maximum water levels: near 1 metre above high astronomical tide. Maximum wave heights: 4 to 6 metres. Locations: Iles de la Madeleine, mainly east facing shorelines. Time span: from 11:00 a.m. AST to 3:00 p.m. AST today. High tide: about 1:00 pm AST today. Remarks: An intensifying low pressure system moving into the Gulf of St. Lawrence today will give a combination of storm surge and rough and pounding waves to produce some coastal flooding along east facing shorelines of the Islands. ### High waves combined with the surge may cause damage along the coast. Coastal erosion is possible in vulnerable areas. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NSstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NSStorm.

properties.Title: Storm Surge Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:

Forillon Park - Gaspé - Percé: 2021-01-17, from 02:30 AM to 06:30 AM. New-Carlisle - Chandler: 2021-01-17, from 03:00 AM to 07:00 AM.
